<Layout title="Methodology">
  <article class="prose prose-invert prose-amber max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h1>How This Library Was Built</h1>
    <p class="lead text-slate-300 text-lg">
      Complete transparency about curation methodology, known biases, and limitations.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/30 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
      <h3 class="text-amber-400 mt-0">⚠️ Key Disclosures</h3>
      <ul class="text-slate-300">
        <li>The library's initial seed sources drew heavily from psi-sympathetic researchers</li>
        <li>Skeptical papers represent 13.8% of the collection (target: 20%)</li>
        <li>All metadata was AI-extracted and may contain errors</li>
        <li>Only freely available papers were included — paywalled works are underrepresented</li>
        <li>The full methodology document is available for inspection</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>What This Library Is</h2>
    <p>A curated collection of 354 scientific publications on psi phenomena — predominantly peer-reviewed journal articles. The collection covers telepathy, precognition, psychokinesis, remote viewing, healing intention, mediumship, near-death experiences, critical and skeptical literature, and methodological discussions. Papers span 1886 to 2025, drawn from 118 journals.</p>
    
    <p><strong>This is not an advocacy resource.</strong> It includes both supportive and critical work. 49 papers (13.8%) occupy the Skeptical and Critical folder. The controversy maps present papers on both sides with equal structural weight.</p>

    <h2>Who Built It</h2>
    <p>A human curator directed AI agents (Anthropic's Claude Code running Opus 4.6) through structured planning documents over 388 sessions across approximately one week. The AI agents designed the architecture, downloaded papers, read full PDFs, extracted metadata, wrote structured summaries, and maintained cross-references.</p>

    <h2>Known Biases</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Seed source bias:</strong> Initial papers drawn from Dean Radin's references and IONS publications</li>
      <li><strong>Access bias:</strong> Only freely available papers included — paywalled skeptical literature is underrepresented</li>
      <li><strong>AI extraction:</strong> Metadata generated by AI, not domain experts — may contain errors</li>
      <li><strong>Temporal bias:</strong> Focuses on post-2000 research; pre-1970 parapsychology is underrepresented</li>
      <li><strong>Publication bias:</strong> Positive results are more likely to be published in any field</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How to Verify</h2>
    <p>Pick any catalog entry, read the PDF, and compare. Check the controversy maps for balance. Review the wishlist for omissions. This library was designed to withstand examination, not to discourage it.</p>

    <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm mt-8">Full methodology document: <code>_METHOD.md</code> in the source repository.</p>
  </article>
</Layout>
